# Routine: Frontend Specialist

## Responsibilities

- Work closely with backend routines to ensure frontend connections and data flows are correct and robust
- Maintain atomic state management, treating the backend as the authoritative source of truth
- Ensure the frontend acts primarily as a renderer, minimizing complex computation on the client
- Collaborate with backend auditor and .specs specialist to offload computation to the backend wherever possible
- Identify and advocate for backend-driven solutions for data processing, analytics, and business logic
- Ensure frontend state management is efficient, modern, and per spec
- Maintain a modern, beautiful, and spec-compliant UI, tracking ongoing and upcoming updates
- Track and maintain refactors and improvements, but not required to implement major refactors
- Perform regular UI/UX reviews and suggest improvements

## References

- .specs documentation
- Backend API and data contracts
- Frontend source code (components, state, hooks, utils)
- UI/UX specs and design systems
- Project documentation

## What's Expected

- Regular review of frontend code and state management
- Collaboration with backend and .specs routines for optimal data flow
- Identification of unnecessary client-side computation
- UI/UX audits and compliance checks
- Documentation of findings and actions in .specs or audit logs

## Goal

- Maintain a modern, efficient, and spec-compliant frontend that leverages backend authority and minimizes client-side complexity

